  "title": "HRBP",
  "description": "<p><strong>Position: HR Business Partnering </strong><br>\n<strong>Location:</strong> One-North<br>\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> HR Director</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are helping our client, looking for a HRBP who will be working closely with R&amp;D team to understand workforce needs, support people plans, and drive talent growth. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong><br>\n</p>\n<p><strong>Talent Development</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Design, manage and enhance learning programmes including New Hire Orientation, General Management tracks, Leadership Development, Professional Conversion, and Earn &amp; Learn programmes.</li>\n  <li>Identify organisational capability needs and partner with business leaders and HRBPs to roll out targeted development initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Build and implement leadership development frameworks to strengthen the capabilities and effectiveness of people managers.</li>\n  <li>Lead the organisation’s career development strategy, ensuring clear frameworks and pathways to support employee growth.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>HR Business Partnering </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Serve as a strategic HR partner to business leaders, advising on workforce planning, performance, development priorities, and succession needs.</li>\n  <li>Lead performance management and talent review cycles, including talent mapping, promotion processes, goal-setting and individual development plans.</li>\n  <li>Support HR operations and projects including payroll coordination, HR policy implementation, and employee lifecycle touchpoints.</li>\n  <li>Prepare HR dashboards, reports and workforce analytics to provide data-driven recommendations to leadership.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of experience in Learning &amp; Development, Talent Management, and HR Business Partnering roles.</li>\n  <li>Able to multitask and work under pressure in a fast-paced, matrixed environment.</li>\n  <li><strong>Mandarin</strong> is required due to the need to communicate with Mandarin speaking students and counterparts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Regrettably, only shortlisted candidates will be notified.Please note that data provided is for recruitment purposes only.</p>\n<p>Business Registration No.: 202004228R | License. No. - 20S0118 </p>",
